Self-Proclaimed Prophet Shepherd Bushiri now faces more than just fraud and money-laundering charges. The Pretoria Magistrates court has authorised three warrants of arrest for rape cases against him. #eNCA Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Three arrest warrants for rape have been authorised against Shepard Bushiri. Bushiri and his wife, Mary, left South Africa after being granted bail. READ: Bushiri holds online church service They were arrested on fraud and money laundering charges. The couple were arrested by Malawian authorities but were later released. Meanwhile, the justice department in South Africa says it plans to serve an extradition letter on Malawi within the next two weeks.